text: I've been messing around with different languages and frameworks to find the right fit and I think at some point it would be nice to make money doing web development.
Likely I would need to start out with freelance projects to find work at first, which I think would be ideal anyway.
My problem is that there really doesn't seem to be much freelance work for the languages I enjoy the most such as Python and Ruby (not even sure about C#).
It seems that the freelance market is dominated by php projects... Is this accurate?
If so, is it a good reason to focus on php while learning?
